// Integer division by a runtime-zero divisor traps on BOTH backends with
// aligned messages : the VM raises `i32.div by zero`
// (`apply_div_mod_binop`, vader/vm/exec.vader) and the native backend routes
// the op through the `vader_div_i32` runtime guard (runtime/c/vader.h), which
// traps identically instead of arm64's silent zero / x86 SIGFPE. Regression
// guard for audit item B2. The divisor is a mutable local so the comptime
// folder leaves the divide for runtime (no C4005) ; `bad_div_zero` covers the
// comptime-folded form.

module "snippet"

main :: fn() -> i32 {
    numerator :: 100
    divisor := 0
    return numerator / divisor
}
